          through the proteasome [ <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">30 31 33</NUMEX> ] . Therefore, <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">group</ENAMEX> I
          mGluR degradation was considered a potential mechanism
          for the decrease in mGluR-mediated calcium current
          <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">modulation</ENAMEX> observed in <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">SCG</ENAMEX> neurons. Although an obvious
          decrease in <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">receptor</ENAMEX> levels in the presence of <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">Siah1a</ENAMEX> was
          not detected (figure <NUMEX TYPE="CARDINAL">3</NUMEX>), it is possible that introduction
